                  . lib. 2. hath worthily chronicled his Grand-fathers remembrance, which was (as hee best witnesseth) called The poore mans King. A title of so inestimable a wealth, that the riches of many Kingdomes are of too low &amp; meane a value, to purchase the dignitie and honour of this onely Style, The

